      "message": "The interface here just feels so error-prone to me that I doubt it will ever work safely. What we need is a clear way to tell a each render thread to pause the processing, drain all incoming messages and save them into a stream. We also need to make sure there\u0027s no parallel accesses to the stream from multiple rendering threads.\nFor snapshot loading it\u0027s even more complicated: RenderThread has to load all its information from the stream and then start the processing when it\u0027s allowed to.\n\nI imagine the interface should be more parallel, as we need to do it quickly. What about the following:\n\nclass Future\u003cT\u003e // a class that holds a value that\u0027s being calculated in a separate thread. T\u0026 get() blocks until that thread has finished\n\nRenderThread {\n    Future\u003cStream\u003e stopAndSaveToStream();\n\n    static RenderThreadPtr createFromStream(Stream*, \n               std::weak_ptr\u003cRendererImpl\u003e renderer,\n               std::shared_ptr\u003cRenderChannelImpl\u003e channel);\n};\n\nThis way we could do it in a loop:\n\nfor (thread : renderThreads) \n    streams.push_back(thread.stopAndSaveToStream();\n\nfor (stream : streams)\n    globalStream.appendFrom(stream.get());",
